# Navigation snippets template reference

All navigation snippet methods are available under the `pt.snippets.navigation` template variable.

## Available methods

<div class="method-ref">
    
    <div class="method">
        <h3 class="method-title" id="snippets-nav-pagetree">pt.snippets.navigation.<span class="name">pageTree([startPage [, opts [, attrs ]]])</span></h3>
        <ul class="variables">
            <li><code>startPage</code>: <em>(optional)</em> Page to start generating the tree structure from. Defaults to homepage. Can be a <a href="{{ pt.pages.getUrlById('pages-order-ids') }}#assigning-ids">page ID</a> or a <a href="{{ pt.pages.getUrlById('template-ref-pages') }}#page-objects">page object</a>.</li>
            <li><code>opts</code>: <em>(optional)</em> Array of configuration options. See below for defaults.</li>
            <li><code>attrs</code>: <em>(optional)</em> Array of additional attributes to set on the opening list tag.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="method-desc">
            <p>Outputs a nested-list page tree structure, useful for generating navigation. The main nav for this documentation (on the left) is generated by it!</p>
        </div>

{% raw %}<pre class="brush: twig">{# Generate a full site page tree, current page is /index.php/about/bar #}
{{ pt.snippets.navigation.pageTree() }}
<ul>
    <li class="level-0 is-parent"><a href="/">Home</a>
        <ul>
            <li class="level-1 is-parent"><a href="/index.php/about">About</a>
                <ul>
                    <li class="level-2"><a href="/index.php/about/foo">Foo</a></li>
                    <li class="level-2 is-current"><a href="/index.php/about/bar">Bar</a></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="level-1"><a href="/index.php/contact">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

{# Generate a tree of subpages of page with ID 'about', current page is /index.php/about/bar #}
{{ pt.snippets.navigation.pageTree('about', {'includeParent':false, 'class':'subnav'}) }}
<ul class="subnav">
    <li class="level-0"><a href="/index.php/about/foo">Foo</a></li>
    <li class="level-0 is-current"><a href="/index.php/about/bar">Bar</a></li>
</ul></pre>{% endraw %}

<h3><code>opts</code> options and defaults</h3>

<p>Below are the default <code>opts</code> values - you can overwrite some or all of these to customise the `pageTree` method's behaviour.</p>

{% raw %}<pre class="brush: twig">{
    'includeParent': true,          {# whether to include the parent item or not #}
    'type': 'ul',                   {# list type tag to use #}
    'maxDepth': null,               {# maximum depth to iterate down to #}
    'levelClassPrefix': 'level-',   {# prefix to use for level classes - set to null to disable #}
    'currentClass': 'is-current',   {# class to apply to the current page li - set to null to disable #}
    'parentClass' : 'is-parent',    {# class to apply to the parent li's of current page - set to null to disable #}
}</pre>{% endraw %}       

    </div>
    
    <div class="method">
        <h3 class="method-title" id="snippets-nav-breadcrumb">pt.snippets.navigation.<span class="name">breadcrumb([ opts [, attrs ]])</span></h3>
        <ul class="variables">
            <li><code>opts</code>: <em>(optional)</em> Array of configuration options. See below for defaults.</li>
            <li><code>attrs</code>: <em>(optional)</em> Array of additional attributes to set on the opening list tag.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="method-desc">
            <p>Outputs a breadcrumb structure using a list. The breadcrumb for this documentation (above) is generated by it!</p>
        </div>

{% raw %}<pre class="brush: twig">{# Generate a full breadcrumb, current page is /index.php/about/bar #}
{{ pt.snippets.navigation.breadcrumb() }}
<ul>
    <li class="level-0"><a href="/">Home</a></li>
    <li class="level-1"><a href="/index.php/about">About</a>
    <li class="level-2 is-current"><em>Bar</em></li>
</ul>

{# Generate a breadcrumb, don't include the homepage, append a couple of items on the end #}
{{ pt.snippets.navigation.breadcrumb({
    'type': 'ol',
    'offset': 1,
    'append': [
        'Foo': '/index.php/example/foo',
        'Hello': '/index.php/hello'
    ]
}) }}
<ol>
    <li class="level-0"><a href="/index.php/about">About</a>
    <li class="level-1"><a href="/index.php/about/bar">Bar</a>
    <li class="level-2"><a href="/index.php/example/foo">Foo</a>
    <li class="level-3 is-current"><em>Hello</em></li>
</ol></pre>{% endraw %}

<h3><code>opts</code> options and defaults</h3>

<p>Below are the default <code>opts</code> values - you can overwrite some or all of these to customise the `pageTree` method's behaviour.</p>

{% raw %}<pre class="brush: twig">{
    'type': 'ul',                   {# list type tag to use #}
    'levelClassPrefix': 'level-',   {# prefix to use for level classes - set to null to disable #}
    'currentClass': 'is-current',   {# class to apply to the current page li - set to null to disable #}
    'offset': 0,                    {# number of items to skip from the start #}
    'limit': null,                  {# maximum number of items to show #}
    'append': [],                   {# array of page objects (or 'title':'url' key/value pairs) to append to the list #}
    'prepend': []                   {# array of page objects (or 'title':'url' key/value pairs) to prepend to the list #}
}</pre>{% endraw %}       

